# Wavefront OBJ — square-base pyramid.
# §3.11 batch 9b.2b — second asset used to exercise multi-mesh
# dispatch in the rpg_demo. Slot 1 in the renderer's mesh table.
# Pickups draw with this shape; player + NPCs continue to use the
# default cube (slot 0).
#
# 5 vertices (apex + 4 base corners) + 6 normals (4 side + 1 base
# + 1 spare) + 6 faces (4 side triangles + 2 base triangles).
# After parsing: 18 corners total (already triangles, so no fan-split
# multiplier — 4 side faces × 3 corners + 2 base faces × 3 corners).

# Apex.
v  0.0  0.5  0.0
# Base corners (-Y plane, corners CCW seen from below).
v -0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5  0.5
v -0.5 -0.5  0.5

# Side normals — slope outward and upward, length-1 approximations.
# Front (-Z), right (+X), back (+Z), left (-X).
vn  0.0  0.4472 -0.8944
vn  0.8944 0.4472  0.0
vn  0.0  0.4472  0.8944
vn -0.8944 0.4472  0.0
# Base normal.
vn  0.0 -1.0  0.0
# Spare slot (unused; vn 6 just keeps indexing tidy).
vn  0.0  1.0  0.0

# Side triangles — apex + two adjacent base corners, CCW from OUTSIDE
# each face. 2026-05-22 audit (round 8) — original windings were
# reversed (CW from outside) so the renderer culled the outside of
# each pyramid; each triangle was flipped from (a,b,c) to (a,c,b).
f 1//1 3//1 2//1
f 1//2 4//2 3//2
f 1//3 5//3 4//3
f 1//4 2//4 5//4
# Base — two triangles (CCW seen from below, i.e. flip ordering vs
# top-down view since the base faces -Y).
f 2//5 4//5 5//5
f 2//5 3//5 4//5
